    "An eect size of 0.2 is about one quarter of a standard deviation of the outcome and corresponds to judges deciding in the conservative direction about 20 percent more often relative to the mean liberal-conservative decision rate.",
    "The eect in the strict specication also holds in the full sample of all judges, including never-attenders (Column 7).",
    "foot_9 Overall, the Manne program pushes economics-related cases in a conservative decision direction, especially relative to non-economics-related cases.",
    "Next we look at voting against federal regulatory agencies, particularly those entrusted with enforcing labor and environmental regulation.",
    "We focus on two types of agencies the Law-and-Economics movement specically criticized: the labor agencies (especially the National Labor Relations Board and Department of Labor) and the Environmental Protection Agency."
